<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1273,1918]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName box="[197,299,1273,1299]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wulpii">
<emphasis box="[197,212,1273,1298]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[226,299,1273,1298]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">wulpii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was included in the last version of the identification key (
<bibRefCitation author="Rozkosny" box="[1066,1369,1273,1299]" pageId="17" pageNumber="30" refString="Rozkosny, R. &amp; Kovac, D. (2003) Seven new species of Ptecticus including new distributional records and a key to the Oriental species. Senckenbergiana biologica, 82, 191 - 211." type="journal article" year="2003">
Rozkošný &amp; Kovac 
<number box="[1307,1369,1273,1299]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Brunetti" box="[307,494,1312,1338]" pageId="17" pageNumber="29" refString="Brunetti, E. (1923) Second revision of the Oriental Stratiomyidae. Records of the Indian Museum, 25, 45 - 180." type="journal article" year="1923">
Brunetti (
<number box="[422,484,1312,1338]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1923.0">1923</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as a new name for 
<taxonomicName authority="Wulp, 1885" authorityName="Wulp" authorityYear="1885" box="[731,1006,1312,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis box="[731,746,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[762,857,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">apicalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wulp" box="[865,1006,1312,1338]" pageId="17" pageNumber="30" refString="Wulp, F. M. van der (1885) On exotic Diptera. Part 2. Notes from the Leyden Museum, 7, 57 - 64." type="journal article" year="1885">
Wulp, 
<number box="[946,1006,1312,1338]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1885.0">1885</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
being reportedly preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew, 1855" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis box="[1413,1428,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,250,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">apicalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Loew" box="[259,410,1350,1376]" pageId="17" pageNumber="29" refString="Loew, H. (1855) Einige Bemerkungen uber die Gattung Sargus. Verhandlungen des zoologisch-botanischen Vereines in Wien, 5 (2), 131 - 148." type="journal article" year="1855">
Loew, 
<number box="[344,410,1350,1376]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1855.0">1855</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Brunetti (l.c.) stated that 
<taxonomicName box="[741,852,1350,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wulpii">
<emphasis box="[741,757,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[774,852,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">wulpii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
“is easily recognised by the black 
<number box="[1294,1308,1350,1376]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="5.0">5</number>
th and 
<number box="[1397,1411,1350,1376]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="6.0">6</number>
th abdominal segments in conjuction with the all orange genitalia“ whereas 
<taxonomicName box="[1020,1174,1389,1415]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanurus">
<emphasis box="[1020,1035,1389,1414]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1050,1174,1389,1414]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">melanurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the abdominal tip beginning from the 
<number box="[388,401,1428,1454]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="5.0">5</number>
th segment completely black. However, we stated that this character is largely variable and examined the 
<typeStatus box="[370,432,1466,1492]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">types</typeStatus>
of both species under discussion. We found that 
<taxonomicName authority="Wulp" authorityName="Wulp" box="[1020,1217,1466,1492]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis box="[1020,1035,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1050,1144,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">apicalis</emphasis>
Wulp
</taxonomicName>
(
<number box="[1235,1250,1466,1492]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="3.0">3</number>
syntypic males from Sumatra and Borneo, deposited in 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34992" box="[636,727,1505,1531]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34992" name="National Museum of Natural History, Naturalis" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">RMNH</collectionCode>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew" authorityName="Loew" box="[795,998,1505,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis box="[795,810,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[826,921,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">apicalis</emphasis>
Loew
</taxonomicName>
(male 
<typeStatus box="[1083,1176,1505,1531]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">syntype</typeStatus>
from „ 
<collectingCountry box="[1261,1319,1505,1531]" name="Iceland" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Pulo</collectingCountry>
Penang“, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,262,1544,1570]" name="Malaysia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, deposited in 
<collectionCode box="[424,511,1544,1570]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">ZMHB</collectionCode>
) are actually conspecific and both identical with the 
<typeStatus box="[1135,1242,1544,1570]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker, 1848" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1848" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanurus">
<emphasis box="[1282,1297,1544,1569]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1312,1435,1544,1569]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">melanurus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Walker" box="[158,318,1582,1608]" pageId="17" pageNumber="30" refString="Walker, F. (1848) List of the specimens of dipterous insects in the collection of the British Museum. Part I. British Museum, London, 229 pp." type="book" year="1848">
Walker, 
<number box="[258,318,1582,1608]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1848.0">1848</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<collectionCode box="[373,464,1582,1608]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">BMNH</collectionCode>
, cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rozkosny" box="[513,702,1582,1608]" pageId="17" pageNumber="30" refString="Rozkosny, R. (2002) A revision of the Oriental Ptecticus species described by G. Enderlein (Stratiomyidae, Diptera). Acta Zoolgica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae, 48, 21 - 33." type="journal article" year="2002">
Rozkošný 
<number box="[638,702,1582,1608]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[721,824,1582,1608]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wulpii">
<emphasis box="[721,736,1583,1608]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[750,824,1583,1608]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">wulpii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is thus a new synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[1137,1290,1582,1608]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanurus" status="syn. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1137,1152,1583,1608]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1166,1290,1583,1608]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">melanurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1297,1402,1582,1608]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">syn. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1273,1918]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
The male 
<typeStatus box="[317,421,1621,1647]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="James, 1950" authorityName="James" authorityYear="1950" box="[462,763,1621,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="okinawae">
<emphasis box="[462,477,1621,1646]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[493,607,1621,1646]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">okinawae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="James" box="[615,763,1621,1647]" pageId="17" pageNumber="29" refString="James, M. T. (1950) Some Stratiomyidae (Diptera) from Okinawa and Guam. Pacific Science, 4 (3), 184 - 187." type="journal article" year="1950">
James, 
<number box="[703,763,1621,1647]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1950.0">1950</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[836,904,1621,1647]" name="Japan" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Japan</collectingCountry>
(Okinawa, Chizuka; deposited in 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34700" box="[1314,1373,1621,1647]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15690" name="California Academy of Sciences" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">CAS</collectionCode>
) was examined (cf. 
<figureCitation box="[327,416,1660,1686]" captionStart="FIGURES 50 – 51" captionStartId="21.[151,269,1395,1419]" captionTargetBox="[471,1110,204,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[471,1116,194,1372]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 50 – 51. Holotype of Ptecticus okinawae James (50) and holotype of Ptecticus japonicus Thunberg (51)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186343/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Fig. 
<number box="[384,416,1660,1686]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="50.0">50</number>
</figureCitation>
) and it was concluded that this specimen agrees with the concept of 
<taxonomicName box="[1259,1373,1660,1686]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurifer">
<emphasis box="[1259,1274,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1290,1373,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">aurifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The metallic bluish reflections mentioned by James are barely discernable and can also be found in other specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[312,421,1737,1763]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurifer">
<emphasis box="[312,326,1737,1762]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[341,421,1737,1762]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">aurifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This synonymy was already suspected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nagatomi" box="[928,1133,1737,1763]" pageId="17" pageNumber="29" refString="Nagatomi, A., (1975) The Sarginae and Pachygasterinae of Japan (Diptera: Stratiomyidae). The Transaction of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 126 (3) (1974), 305 - 421." type="journal article" year="1975">
Nagatomi (
<number box="[1060,1124,1737,1763]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1975.0">1975</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1273,1918]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
A comparison of recently collected specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[782,902,1776,1802]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kerteszi">
<emphasis box="[782,797,1776,1801]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[812,902,1776,1801]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">kerteszi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[974,1031,1776,1802]" name="Laos" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Laos</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1090,1194,1776,1802]" name="Thailand" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Thailand</collectingCountry>
with the description and figures of 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang &amp; Yang, 1995" authorityName="Yang &amp; Yang" authorityYear="1995" box="[323,756,1814,1840]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhejiangensis">
<emphasis box="[323,338,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[353,511,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">zhejiangensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yang" box="[519,756,1814,1840]" pageId="17" pageNumber="30" refString="Yang, D. &amp; Yang, C. (1995) Diptera: Stratiomyidae. Pp. 490 - 492, In: Hong, W. U. (ed.), Insects of Baishanzu Mountains. Eastern China. China Forestry Publishing House, Beijing, i - xiii, 586 pp." type="book chapter" year="1995">
Yang &amp; Yang, 
<number box="[695,756,1814,1840]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, resulted in the conclusion that both species are identical. Consequently, 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang &amp; Yang, 1995" authorityName="Yang &amp; Yang" authorityYear="1995" box="[325,754,1853,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhejiangensis">
<emphasis box="[325,339,1853,1878]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[355,513,1853,1878]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">zhejiangensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yang" box="[520,754,1853,1879]" pageId="17" pageNumber="30" refString="Yang, D. &amp; Yang, C. (1995) Diptera: Stratiomyidae. Pp. 490 - 492, In: Hong, W. U. (ed.), Insects of Baishanzu Mountains. Eastern China. China Forestry Publishing House, Beijing, i - xiii, 586 pp." type="book chapter" year="1995">
Yang &amp; Yang, 
<number box="[695,754,1853,1879]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the Zhejijang Province in SE 
<collectingCountry box="[1173,1243,1853,1879]" name="China" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">China</collectingCountry>
is a syn. nov. of 
<taxonomicName authority="De Meijere, 1924" authorityName="De Meijere" authorityYear="1924" box="[151,480,1892,1918]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Ptecticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kerteszi">
<emphasis box="[151,166,1892,1917]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[180,269,1892,1917]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">kerteszi</emphasis>
de 
<bibRefCitation author="Meijere" box="[312,480,1892,1918]" pageId="17" pageNumber="29" refString="Meijere, J. C. H. de (1924) Studien uber sudostasiatische Dipteren XV. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 67, 1 - 64." type="journal article" year="1924">
Meijere, 
<number box="[418,480,1892,1918]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1924.0">1924</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
